SIMPLE: dispark
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dispark
<hw>Dis*park"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
throw (a park or inclosure); to treat (a private park) as a
common.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Gentiles were made to be God's people when the Jews' inclosure
was <qex>disparked</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To set at large; to release from
inclosure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Till his free muse threw down the pale,⟦br⟧
And did at once <qex>dispark</qex> them all.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disparkle</ent>⟦br⟧
